text: Good to hear your background. It is essential in your life to get involved in something you like. Forget about making big $$$. This is the wrong focus. Focus on doing what makes you feel good. It is super hard to make money doing what you do not like to do. But sometimes what you think is really fun can not make any $. Then do it as a hobby and get a job that are still at least half fun. Doing it as a hobby also have the advantage that you can do all the fun part of it as you do not have to care about someone paying for it.

text: Really informative. I don't normally watch videos about personal YouTubers (typically just get the info I need and get out) but your channel is more than that to me. I am a double major in accounting and comp sci, so finance is obviously a big thing with me, and it looks like you are very familiar with both of those segments as well.   I hope to watch all of your videos, absorb as much information I can, and actually do something great.   You are like a professor that I get to know... but has no idea who I am! author: @davidnelson4563
text: I'm curious what your thoughts are about "formal" CS education, particularly since you said you don't have any.  I'm currently a student at Georgia Tech's relatively new completely online MS in CS. My undergraduate background was not in this field and so I've been playing a lot of catch up. Your videos have helped a lot with that and I'm very grateful (thanks!). It seems CS is ideally suited for this type of online education, and I imagine eventually there will be undergraduate programs available online as well. Along the way, the whole college model may be altered. I guess I mention this because a lot of what you do seems to supplement the more formal online education now available. In terms of business ideas, I think it would be worth exploring.
